Ask HN: Ex-users of CentOS, what do you run now?
text:
Are you still on CentOS?

Did you try AlmaLinux?

Did you try Rocky Linux?

Which distro did you land on as a replacement for CentOS on your servers?

How did you end up at the choice, and do you think you are likely to continue to run that distro?

It’s been roughly one year since RedHat terminated development of CentOS. It’d be interesting to know where people in the HN crowd who used to rely on CentOS have turned to since then.

Ask HN: Are ML models like ChatGPT just compressing/decompressing information?
text:
Disclaimer: I don't really understand how these magical AI models do their thing but, like almost everyone else I've been playing around with ChatGPT and I'm totally blown away by it.

It seems like every time I submit a question to chatGPT, I imagine some fancy math is being done behind the scenes and I am getting fed back some information from this massive model "file".

Is the model just a compressed representation of all the training data that the model was trained on and so sending back a response is just 'decompressing' the part of the model that is relevant to my question and sending me back the requested information? (I imagine it hallucinates the parts that vary from the data it was trained on to give a best-guess response to my query).

Wonder if there are any experts on here that could confirm/deny my intuitive guess here.

Ask HN: Direct Zoom call lighting with large screens in the way?
text:
I want to explore some direct lighting options for Zoom calls, but I have a couple of 32" screens in the way here, without much space on the sides.

I've looked at ring lights but they seem to need a lot of space, and they'd have to be offset quite a bit due to the setup of the screens here.

Are there any direct-type video call lights to recommend that are compact and effective enough to work in this kind of situation?

(Indirect lighting is taken care of pretty well already)

Ask HN: I want to interview people. Should I start a podcast or something else?
text:
I want to interview interesting people and the people that inspire me in general. I'm friendly and personable but I'm not big on socializing and definitely have no "radio personality". I just really enjoy talking to interesting people and digging their brains and hearing their wisdom.

Starting a podcast is an obvious option but the podcasting space seems so saturated now, especially for the topics I have in mind (eg creative routines, working towards your dreams). Are there other formats for interviewing people?

How are these advanced technology transforming the gaming experience?
text:
One of the most exciting developments in gaming space is the intersection of Virtual & Augmented Reality and Artificial Intelligence (AR, VR, and AI). With the emergence of these advanced technology, the gaming experience has been transformed in ways we never thought possible. We must get a better idea of what these technologies have to offer and how they're changing the gaming landscape, where reality and fantasy are blurred and players can interact with both. It's also about the potential of AI technology in this new gaming era and we need to compares augmented reality to virtual reality systems to understand the differences between AR vs VR.
